    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>No Transportation Funds for Sanctuary Cities Act</b></p> <p>This bill prohibits the obligation or expenditure of certain national infrastructure investment funds for discretionary grants (commonly known as Transportation Investment Generating Economic Recovery [TIGER] grants) for a surface transportation infrastructure investment project in a sanctuary jurisdiction.</p> <p>A &quot;sanctuary jurisdiction&quot; means a state or political subdivision that prohibits or restricts a government entity or official from:</p> <ul> <li>receiving, maintaining, or providing a federal, state, or local government entity information regarding the citizenship or immigration status of an individual; or </li> <li>complying with a Department of Homeland Security (DHS) detainer order to temporarily hold an alien in custody, transport an alien to federal custody, or notify DHS about an alien's release.</li> </ul>]]></text>
          <actionDate>2017-02-02</actionDate>
